3) Folder structure 


4) How Angular Application start/ bootstraping process of angular app 

  to start application- "ng serve" or " npm run start"
   --> package.json --> script-> start--> Angular.json--> main.ts--> bootstrapmodule(Appmodule)
   --> Bootstarp;[Appcomponent] --> appcomponent--> selector name --> index.html



5) Modules
   How to create module- "ng g m [Name of module]"
   e.g- ng g m registration

   how to create module with routing file
   eg. ng g m registration --routing

   --registration.module.ts.
   @ngModule{
    declaration: []  -- we need add components which we are using in this module inside declaration 
    array;
    imports: []  ---- we can import other modules
   } - decorator



6) COMPONENT-
   -- cmd to create component- "ng g c [name of component]
   e.g- ng g c login-page

   it craetes 4 file
   1) html - html code /view/ template
   2) css - styling
   3) spec.ts- 
   4) .ts- functionality

   ts- typescript


7) Data Binding
   Types of data binding
   1) One way data binding
   2) Two way data binding

   1) One way data binding-
     A) interpolation / string interpolation- it bind data from .ts to .html - syntax {{name of variable}} ;
     B) Property - it bind data from .ts to .html - syntac [name of variable] ;
     C) Event - it bind data from .html to .ts - syntac (name of event);
     e.g. click, moushover

   2) Two way data binding
     A) ngModel - syntax [(ngModel)]
